title: Muddy Waters - Document Records (1941-1950, FLAC)
description: These essential songs largely recorded by Alan Lomax show the power and intensity of Muddy Waters performing acoustic Mississippi Delta Blues.  After 1950, Waters would travel north to Chicago and find himself switching to electric guitar to be heard in the much louder and rowdy urban bars.  He would sign with Chess Records and along with Howlin' Wolf, begin honing the singular sound of Chicago Blues. Enjoy!
